The '''Makira honeyeater''' ('''''Meliarchus sclateri'''''), also known as the '''San Cristobal honeyeater''', is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Meliphagidae]].
It is [[Endemism|endemic]] to [[Makira]] in the Solomon Islands.

